&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;13&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; --tenant-id &lt;span style="color:#4e9a06"&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000"&gt;TENANT_ID&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#4e9a06"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#4e9a06"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;14&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; --multi-tenant-app-name &lt;span style="color:#4e9a06"&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000"&gt;MULTI_TENANT_APP_NAME&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#4e9a06"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#4e9a06"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;15&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; --consent-url &lt;span style="color:#4e9a06"&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000"&gt;CONSENT_URL&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#4e9a06"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#4e9a06"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;16&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; --default-base-location &lt;span style="color:#4e9a06"&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000"&gt;DEFAULT_BASE_LOCATION&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#4e9a06"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#4e9a06"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;17&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; my_azure_catalog
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>Migrating from Existing Iceberg Catalogs</title><link>https://polaris.apache.org/releases/1.3.0/getting-started/creating-a-catalog/catalog-migration/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://polaris.apache.org/releases/1.3.0/getting-started/creating-a-catalog/catalog-migration/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;There are two ways to migrate an existing Iceberg catalog to Polaris:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using the &lt;a href="https://github.com/apache/polaris-tools/blob/main/iceberg-catalog-migrator/README.md"&gt;Iceberg Catalog Migrator tool&lt;/a&gt;: A command-line tool to migrate Iceberg tables from one Iceberg catalog to another. This tool works with any existing Iceberg catalog including Polaris.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using the &lt;a href="https://github.com/apache/polaris-tools/blob/main/polaris-synchronizer/README.md"&gt;Polaris Synchronizer tool&lt;/a&gt;: A tool to migrate entities from one Polaris instance to another. This tool is specific to Polaris.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Both of these tools are available in the &lt;a href="https://github.com/apache/polaris-tools"&gt;Polaris-Tools repository&lt;/a&gt;. Please refer to the relevant README.md documentation for more information.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>